@node "ParentDir" "Parent directory"
Parent directory
================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Reads the parent directory, and display it.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      First the parent directory is searched  in the buffers.  If it is not
  found,  it is directly read from the device.  If this  function is called
  whereas the source directory is the root,  the @{"Reread directory" LINK GetDir} function
  is called.

@endnode


@node "RootDir" "Root directory"
Root directory
==============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Reads the root directory.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "GetDir" "Reread directory"
Reread directory
================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Forces to read and display the source directory again.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      The current selection will be lost.

@endnode


@node "SelectDir" "Select a directory"
Select a directory
==================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Opens a requester to select the directory to display.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      This function requires reqtools.library.

@endnode


@node "SelectBuffer" "Select buffer"
Select buffer
=============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      A requester is opened to select a directory among the buffers.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "ClearBuffers" "Clear buffers"
Clear buffers
=============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      To clear several directories among the buffers.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Tree" "Tree"
Tree
====

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      A window is opened to display all  directories and sub-directories of
  the current volume. Then you may select a directory.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      All the directories are stored in the buffers. So using this function
  sometimes needs lots of memory.

@endnode


@node "ReadDir" "Read directory"
Read directory
==============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      This  function reads  selected  directories and  stores  them in  the
  buffers. They are not displayed in the current window.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      Read sub-directories :
          Sub-directories will be read and stored as well.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      Directories read can be displayed using the @{"Select buffer" LINK SelectBuffer} function.

@endnode


@node "DiskInfo" "Disk informations"
Disk informations
=================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Displays informations about current device.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "SwapWindows" "Swap windows"
Swap windows
============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      The left  window is displayed in the right window,  and the right one
  is displayed in the left one.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "ToggleSD" "Toggle source/destination"
Toggle source/destination
=========================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      The source window  becomes  the destination.  The  destination window
  becomes the source window.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "All" "Select all entries"
Select all entries
==================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Select all files and directories of the source directory.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Clear" "Clear selection"
Clear selection
===============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Unselect all files and directories of the source directory.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Toggle" "Toggle selection"
Toggle selection
================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Selected  entries  become  unselected,  and  unselected  ones  become
  selected.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Select" "Select entries"
Select entries
==============

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Select entries that match with the entered pattern.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Hunt" "Hunt files"
Hunt files
==========

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Search for  files  that match with the  entered  pattern.  Files  are
  searched in the selected directories.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "MemorizeSelection" "Memorize selection"
Memorize selection
==================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Memorizes  selected  entries.  You may  restore  them  using @{"Restore" LINK RestoreSelection}
  @{"selection" LINK RestoreSelection}.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      See @{"Restore selection" LINK RestoreSelection}.

@endnode


@node "RestoreSelection" "Restore selection"
Restore selection
=================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Select entries memorized with Memorize selection, if they exist.  All
  the other entries will be unselected.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Toggle selection :
      Instead of being selected, memorized entries will be unselected.  The
  other ones will be selected.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      Example : Imagine  you want to  unarchive  files to RAM: to  test new
  utilities.  Therefore many files and directories appears in RAM:, and you
  will have to delete them.  But RAM: also contains the "Clipboards", "ENV"
  and "T" directories,  that  you must not delete.  So  before  unarchiving
  anything,  select  these three  directories  and @{"memorize the selection" LINK  MemorizeSelection}.
  Then unarchive and test what you want.  Next restore the selection  (with
  the  toggle selection  option).  All  entries  are  selected  except  the
  "Clipboards", "ENV" and "T" directories.  And you only  have to  call the
  @{"delete" LINK Delete} function.

@endnode


@node "Copy" "Copy"
Copy
====

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      All selected entries will be copied  from the source  to the destina-
  tion directory.  Moreover the program calculates and displays the size of
  all the copied directories (see @{"Calculate directory size" LINK GetSize}).

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Copy date : 
      If this option  is not active,  date of the copied files  will be the
  current date. Else it will be the source files date.

  Copy protection :
      If this  option is active,  the  protection bits  of the copied files
  will be identical to the ones of the source files. Else RWED bits will be
  active.

  Copy comment :
      If the source entry has a comment it will be copied.

  Ask for name :
      Ordering will ask you to type the name of the destination entry. This
  option is like the "Copy as" function in some other tools.

  Low memory :
      This option allows to  reduce memory usage during the copy.  Ordering
  will only use a 11 kB buffer. But files of more than 11 kB will be copied
  several times, and this is much slower.

  Copy icon as well :
      If an icon is associated to a file or a directory, it will be copied,
  even it is not selected.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      Some words  about the "Copy date" option : if  you copy a  directory,
  dates of some sub-directories might be wrong.  But it is not an  Ordering
  bug. It seems to be impossible to copy the date of a sub-directory, and I
  don't know why.

@endnode


@node "Move" "Move"
Move
====

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Selected entries are @{"copied" LINK Copy}  to the  destination directory  and then
  are @{"deleted" LINK Delete},  except if the source device and the destination device are
  the same. In this case, entries are directly moved.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Copy date : 
      If this option  is not active,  date of the copied files  will be the
  current date. Else it will be the source files date.

  Copy protection :
      If this  option is active,  the  protection bits  of the copied files
  will be identical to the ones of the source files. Else RWED bits will be
  active.

  Copy comment :
      If the source entry has a comment it will be copied.

  Ask for name :
      Ordering will ask you to type the name of the destination entry. This
  option is like the "Copy as" function in some other tools.

  Low memory :
      This option is only  available if source and destination  devices are
  different.  It allows to reduce  memory usage during  the copy.  Ordering
  will only use a 11 kB buffer. But files of more than 11 kB will be copied
  in several times, and this is much slower.

  Copy icon as well :
      If an icon is associated to a file or a directory, it will be copied,
  even it is not selected.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Clone" "Clone"
Clone
=====

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Duplicates selected files and directories.  Ordering asks you to type
  the name of the duplicated entries.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Copy date : 
      If this option  is not active,  date of the copied files  will be the
  current date. Else it will be the source files date.

  Copy protection :
      If this  option is active,  the  protection bits  of the copied files
  will be identical to the ones of the source files. Else RWED bits will be
  active.

  Copy comment :
      If the source entry has a comment it will be copied.

  Ask for name :
      This option doesn't do anything with this function.

  Low memory :
      This option allows to  reduce memory usage during the copy.  Ordering
  will only use a 11 kB buffer. But files of more than 11 kB will be copied
  several times, and this is much slower.

  Copy icon as well :
      If an icon is associated to a file or a directory, it will be copied,
  even it is not selected.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Delete" "Delete"
Delete
======

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Deletes selected entries.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Confirm at the beginning :
      Ordering will ask you a confirmation,  then it will delete everything
  selected.

  Confirm for each entry :
      Ordering will ask you a confirmation for each deletion.

  Auto remove protection :
      If a file to delete is protected from deletion (D bit set),  Ordering
  will remove the protection, then it will delete the file.  If this option
  is not active,  Ordering will ask you a  confirmation before deleting the
  file.

  Delete icon as well :
      Even if not selected, the icon associated to a file to delete will be
  deleted as well

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "MakeDir" "Create directory"
Create directory
================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Creates a new directory. Ordering will ask you to type its name.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Add icon :
      Creates an icon associated with the directory.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


@node "Rename" "Rename"
Rename
======

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Renames selected entries.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Rename icon as well :
      If the file or  the directory to rename has an icon,  it will also be
  renamed.
      Example : imagine  you  want  to  rename  the file  "NoFastMem"  into
  "NoFast"; the file "NoFastMem.info" will be renamed into "NoFast.info".

  Re-examine :
      This option has been designed only because of the peecees mediocrity.
  It affects PC0: disks (CrossDOSFileSystem).  Filenames can't be more than
  8 characters long,  and they have to be upper case.  Moreover, many chars
  are forbidden.  However, even if you don't apply these rules, the OS will
  manage the name so that it suits,  and no error will be generated.  So if
  you try to rename the file  "PICTURE.LBM" into  "Beautiful Picture.ilbm",
  Ordering will display "Beautiful Picture.ilbm" in the window.  But if you
  @{"read the directory again" LINK GetDir}, the file will appear as  "BEAUTIFU.ILB".  This
  option allows to read informations  directly from the disk,  and prevents
  Ordering from displaying a bad filename.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      Peecees are very bad computers.

@endnode


@node "GetSize" "Calculate directory size"
Calculate directory size
========================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Calculates the size (in bytes) used by all the files  in the selected
  directories.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


