@node "ShowPic" "Show ILBM picture"
Show ILBM picture
=================

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Displays an IFF-ILBM picture.  When the picture is displayed, you may
  press space  to show or  to hide the pointer.  To come  back to  the main
  program,  press the  left mousebutton.  Press  ESC  to abort  the showing
  sequence.
      You may also display the first frame of an animation (IFF-ANIM).

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

  Force DBLPAL/DBLNTSC :
      Tries to  open the  screen in  DBLPAL or  DBLNTSC.  If it fails,  the
  screen will be opened with the resolution given in the picture.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      This viewer is fast,  but it uses more  memory  than the other  ones,
  because the file is entirely loaded.  I have never found pictures that do
  not work with my viewer. But if you have such images, please send them to
  @{"me" LINK Address} (I will send your disk back to you).  Moreover, I couldn't test it on
  an Amiga with a graphic card.  So it may crash with pictures of more than
  eight bitplanes. If you have problems, please write @{"me" LINK Address}.  I would like to
  get any documentation about these cards (software).

@endnode


@node "ShowIcon" "Show icon"
Show icon
=========

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}

      Displays selected icons. This function supports NewIcons.

@{b}OPTIONS@{ub}

      None.

@{b}COMMENT@{ub}

      None.

@endnode


